<subSubSection id="C3496526FFDBFFBED6B93B2D0262016F" box="[151,619,1544,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="261" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BEC36ADFFDBFFBED6B93B2D0262016F" blockId="1.[151,619,1544,1570]" box="[151,619,1544,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="261">
<heading id="D0A481C1FFDBFFBED6B93B2D0262016F" bold="true" box="[151,619,1544,1570]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="261" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B927EABFFFDBFFBED6B93B2D0262016F" bold="true" box="[151,619,1544,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="261">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D2EFFDBFFBED6CC3B2D0262016F" authority="Hoffman, 1982" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="1982" box="[226,619,1544,1570]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="1" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Sandalodesmini">
Sandalodesmini 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B5CFFDBFFBED79F3B2D0262016F" author="Hoffman, R. L." box="[433,619,1544,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="261" pagination="247 - 259" refId="ref5695" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1982) Chelodesmid studies. XVIII. A synopsis of the genus Sandalodesmus Silvestri, 1902, and proposal of the new tribe Sandalodesmini (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Spixiana, 5 (3), 247 - 259. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 28194567" type="journal article" year="1982">Hoffman, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3496526FFDBFFBED6B93B75014201B7" pageId="1" pageNumber="261" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEC36ADFFDBFFBED6B93B75014201B7" blockId="1.[151,1436,1616,1786]" pageId="1" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="B927EABFFFDBFFBED6B93B75011D0127" bold="true" box="[151,276,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="261">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C534D2EFFDBFFBED7333B7501D90127" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="1982" box="[285,464,1616,1642]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Sandalodesmini">Sandalodesmini</taxonomicName>
males are distinguishable by the gonopods notably reduced in size, entire telopodite subequal to or smaller than gonocoxa, presence of a spiniform process on gonocoxa, cannula modified (except in some species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D2EFFDBFFBED75A3BBD022B01FF" authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1902" box="[372,546,1688,1714]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Sandalodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="1" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B927EABFFFDBFFBED75A3BBD022B01FF" box="[372,546,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="261">Sandalodesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), prefemoral process simple, without additional processes, acropodite process forming a broad shield that protect the solenomere, strongly curved and concealing the solenomere (modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B5CFFDBFFBED6B93BC5013601B7" author="Hoffman, R. L." box="[151,319,1760,1786]" pageId="1" pageNumber="261" pagination="247 - 259" refId="ref5695" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1982) Chelodesmid studies. XVIII. A synopsis of the genus Sandalodesmus Silvestri, 1902, and proposal of the new tribe Sandalodesmini (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Spixiana, 5 (3), 247 - 259. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 28194567" type="journal article" year="1982">Hoffman 1982</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
